examples.en: I drifted into an uneasy sleep.
The snow had drifted our tracks.
She drifted from job to job.
He drifted in and out of consciousness.
The stock market drifted upward.
The crowd drifted out after the performance.
Columns of smoke and ashes drifted to the south-east.
They drifted slowly down river.
I drifted all over the world, I searched everyplace. (D. Bowie, Be My Wife)
The conversation drifted from topic to topic.
I drifted off in a daydream during the class.
The dollar drifted lower against the yen today.
The snow drifted against the side of the house.
The shipwrecked boat drifted away from the shore.
The crisis continued as Britain drifted towards war.
My thoughts drifted back to the time when we first met.
After he left the army he just drifted for a few years.
The unknown young man drifted among the invited guests.
Lewis and his father drifted apart after he moved to New York.
The party guests drifted from room to room, eating and mingling.
Two of Jane's friends drifted in last night, and are staying here.
Other members of the committee drifted in for a quick one before closing time.
